<item>
            <title>[LU-19301] osd_declare_xattr_set() may declare too many credits</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19301</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;each osd_declare_xattr_set() declares LDISKFS_MAXQUOTAS_INIT_BLOCKS(sb) which is not tiny on its own. if number of xattrs is significant (e.g. migration), then number of credits can get huge causing warnings and transaction restarts.&lt;br/&gt;
but actually we need to declare this only once.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
